<h3>Presentation Must Haves</h3>

<p>If you're giving presentations or sharing screensÂ often, I have a couple of recommendations.</p>

<p>
  The first suggestion is <a href="http://carnackeys.com/" target="_blank">Carnac</a>. Presenters tend to forget that 
  the viewers don't know when you press Alt, Ctrl, etc. This is a little application displays those special combination 
  keystrokes so that your audience doesn't get lost when you're flying around Visual Studio using only the keyboard.
</p>

<p>
  The second is <a href="http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/sysinternals/bb897434.aspx" target="_blank">ZoomIt</a>. 
  This application allows you to Zoom in and out of any application running in Windows. It also has some markup 
  features which are quite nice once you get used to the keyboard shortcuts.
</p>

